<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-12-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-01-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                            <head>278. Editorial Note</head>
                            <p>President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> and Prime
                                Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>,
                                accompanied by members of their parties, were guests at a dinner on
                                March 22 given by the Governor of Bermuda, Sir <persName>John
                                    Woodall</persName>, at his residence. (Eisenhower Library,
                                President’s Appointment Book)</p>
                        </div>
